# physics-algorithms

## Casting Trajectory System
Importance Score: 85/100

Core physics components:

1. Line/Rope Physics (src/physics/ropePhysics.js)
- Multi-segment rope simulation with 8 connected points
- Spring-based tension modeling for fishing line behavior
- Wind influence factors affecting line movement
- Water surface interaction detection and response

2. Casting Arc Calculator (src/physics/castTrajectory.js)
- Parabolic trajectory generation with air resistance
- Modifiable launch angle (0-85 degrees)
- Power-based initial velocity scaling
- Environmental factor considerations:
  - Wind speed/direction effects
  - Water surface distance calculation
  - Terrain collision detection

3. Water Surface Interaction (src/water/surfacePhysics.js)
- Dynamic ripple generation on line entry
- Buoyancy calculations for floating tackle
- Wave height influence on surface detection
- Depth-based resistance modeling

4. Rod Tip Physics (src/physics/rodTip.js)
- Spring-based animation system
- Load-responsive bend calculations
- Natural oscillation during idle state
- Cast power influence on tip behavior

Notable mechanics:
- Rod tip flexes realistically based on cast power
- Line segments respond to water surface tension
- Casting trajectory adapts to environmental conditions
- Dynamic ripple generation at line entry points

